                <h1>What Does the Headless Horseman Symbolize?</h1>
                <p>The Headless Horseman represents the fear of the unknown and the consequences of unresolved conflicts. Often interpreted as a ghostly figure haunting the living, he symbolizes loss, vengeance, and the struggle between good and evil. This iconic character embodies the darker aspects of human nature and the haunting legacy of our past actions.</p>
